{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KMXsfxsh2yFqu1wPZFQgoz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Build is green. Here's a summary of what was produced:\n\n**Harness:** `h5_obj_visit_fuzzer` (`h5_obj_visit_fuzzer.c`)\n\n**Attack surface covered:**\n- `H5Oget_info3` — called on the root object with `H5O_INFO_ALL` and on every object opened inside callbacks\n- `H5Literate2` — invoked three times on the root group: name-index/native, creation-order/increasing, and name-index/decreasing\n- `H5Lget_val` — called for every soft link found during iteration, with a 64 KiB cap on allocation to avoid harness OOM\n- `H5Oopen` — called in both the link-iterator callback (for hard/soft links) and the object-visitor callback (for every visited sub-object)\n- `H5Ovisit3` — two full recursive traversals: name-index/native and creation-order/increasing\n- `H5Oclose` — closes every object opened above\n\n**Safety measures:**\n- File opened `H5F_ACC_RDONLY` — no harness-side mutations to file metadata\n- External links (`H5L_TYPE_EXTERNAL`) are skipped in the link callback to avoid filesystem access beyond `/tmp`\n- `MAX_CB_CALLS = 2000` hard cap in both callbacks prevents infinite loops on circular/deeply nested graphs\n- `H5Eset_auto2(H5E_DEFAULT, NULL, NULL)` suppresses error noise\n- Temp file cleaned up with `unlink` on every exit path\n- All harness-owned buffers are properly bounded and freed"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":128,"cache_read_input_tokens":46791,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":128,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f3efc725-4f90-4072-9e90-a474caea2874","uuid":"867639db-3f09-4146-beeb-ee272425cd94"}
